<paragraph id="8B6364E5927BFCEA95AD68BB74FB589D" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">The Republic of Korea.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BFDB508EEB09B4D31EB05A813B24DC51" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="EA1C77F3D8EE1A21E87D17E8AA628364" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="432A261FB2A0D984CDC3EA8A41BA377F" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="E029E8A8A1D43FA28B550F4A12ED1561" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis vellerea" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vellerea">
<emphasis id="119A221B5FCA746A7B07365A1CF10AFB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis vellerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FEDF6B110CB2F1E2B268175016466ACC" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. menehune" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis id="92B751B026D24B7FEDB87B3F0D160DD7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="58A596CD89DA59CCC2882BC72AE1D502" genus="G." lsidName="G. spongiosus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="spongiosus">
<emphasis id="C3653F68309F6228544B3B4D19E6EA5C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">G. spongiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Halling. 
<taxonomicName id="03D8481E4A82ECEFDCC2CCC7892351E3" authorityName="R.H.Petersen" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Desjardin, Halling &amp; Hemmes" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis menehune" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis id="FA1609906C39E3808D8B0DF03E0A960B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a paler stipe, a smaller pileus (8-30 mm), and fewer lamellulae (4-6 series) (
<bibRefCitation id="DD13EAAC880720802DB01868A7D7FF0D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="166 - 176" refId="B10" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Hemmes, DE, 1999. Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus. Mycologia 91 (1): 166 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" title="Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" volume="91" year="1999">Desjardin et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CBC192B1A11860F1665D1840364DBD69" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Agaricaceae" genus="Gymnopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gymnopus spongiosus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="spongiosus">
<emphasis id="8ED98D6C767DC02D06077AD737E8E256" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Gymnopus spongiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a smaller pileus (8-20 mm) and longer stipe (20-55 mm). Micromorphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="97D1D3CFDB1A6298FD4DD0764560922E" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. menehune" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis id="2F637934C8E2C4B1B99D7D7891435CEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has larger basidiospores, basidia, and caulocystidia (
<bibRefCitation id="02DB30EB25AA09ED9C8DB6AE5041956C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="166 - 176" refId="B10" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Hemmes, DE, 1999. Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus. Mycologia 91 (1): 166 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" title="Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" volume="91" year="1999">Desjardin et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="5EB115E503AE78577C328C2FBFB0D08F" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Agaricaceae" genus="Gymnopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gymnopus spongiosus" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="spongiosus">
<emphasis id="31BDA72B3EBBE42DE38A93B825A5096C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Gymnopus spongiosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="091B5CFDF89B5D95685157AEBF180976" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. vellerea" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="vellerea">
<emphasis id="5C89DFD0A80436CEEBA447675BA04D1B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. vellerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that its pileipellis is a 
<taxonomicName id="7E758288C70C34274C0C9FCE66080A17" authorityName="Quelet" authorityYear="1886" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Strophariaceae" genus="Dryophila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dryophila" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E8C0375569F57395E55B51E197ACFF52" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Dryophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-type cutis and its color changes in alkalies. Furthermore, its basidia (18-25 
<normalizedToken id="B1CD3FAA8DCE14E6DF20A2D4FB37A1E3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-9 
<normalizedToken id="F43814105124E93FF336BB0B4E5A319A" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) and trama hyphae (3.5-17 
<normalizedToken id="4C9EB7D17B4F721B8707E156BBA0CD66" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) are thicker and its caulocystidia (3.5-10.5 
<normalizedToken id="C10824FB86632374AC01A5160A26B161" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
broad) are smaller (
<bibRefCitation id="8A6B984249B7B3DB9AE751E709245AB1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2807862" author="Halling, RE" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="487 - 494" refId="B14" refString="Halling, RE, 1996. Notes on Collybia V. Gymnopus section Levipedes in tropical South America with comments on Collybia. Brittonia 48 (4): 487 - 494, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2807862" title="Notes on Collybia V. Gymnopus section Levipedes in tropical South America with comments on Collybia." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2807862" volume="48" year="1996">Halling 1996</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="59EB8B910264C430133637EC84415EA2" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis vellerea" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vellerea">
<emphasis id="800C2714816831D850529C54F4FDDA25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis vellerea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="3A272E1BF9A1A2DC3B49EEB4AFC5469C" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. omphalodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="omphalodes">
<emphasis id="A1C59E48E0F3E25F4FB94180E1A0447B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. omphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="CF1D5F8A9681BFDAAC58592CB41C5FF8" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Kim &amp; Cho &amp; Park &amp; Park &amp; Kim &amp; Kim &amp; Lim" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis omphalodes" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="omphalodes">
<emphasis id="5082153E55CB4FA05F0B69872F7E5BEA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis omphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having smaller basidiomata (20-30 mm) and its habit on logs (
<bibRefCitation id="F0AE7D7F85A6C2F647B7D2B3CE61F391" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(51)80030-5" author="Dennis, R" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the British Mycological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="411 - 482" refId="B7" refString="Dennis, R, 1951. Some Agaricaceae of Trinidad and Venezuela. Leucosporae: Part I. Transactions of the British Mycological Society 34 (4): 411 - 482, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(51)80030-5" title="Some Agaricaceae of Trinidad and Venezuela. Leucosporae: Part I." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0007-1536(51)80030-5" volume="34" year="1951">Dennis 1951</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
